From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: VIKINGYFY <vikingyfy@immortalwrt.org>
Date: Sat, 2 May 2026 00:00:00 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] arm64: dts: qcom: ipq8074: remove pinctrl from uart3 and i2c2

On kernel 6.18, the blsp1_uart3 pinctrl (hsuart_pins: GPIO 46-49) and
blsp1_i2c2 pinctrl (i2c_0_pins: GPIO 42-43) cause GPIO conflicts with
many IPQ807X devices that use these pins for LEDs, buttons, etc.

The pinctrl configuration was not present in kernel 6.12, and removing
it restores the previous behavior where pins are not claimed exclusively
by serial/i2c drivers, allowing them to be used as GPIOs.

Devices that actually need blsp1_uart3 or blsp1_i2c2 for specific
hardware functions can re-enable the pinctrl in their device DTS.

Signed-off-by: VIKINGYFY <vikingyfy@immortalwrt.org>
---
 arch/arm64/boot/dts/qcom/ipq8074.dtsi | 4 ----
 1 file changed, 4 deletions(-)

--- a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/qcom/ipq8074.dtsi
+++ b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/qcom/ipq8074.dtsi
@@ -690,8 +690,6 @@
 			dmas = <&blsp_dma 4>,
 				<&blsp_dma 5>;
 			dma-names = "tx", "rx";
-			pinctrl-0 = <&hsuart_pins>;
-			pinctrl-names = "default";
 			status = "disabled";
 		};
 
@@ -747,8 +745,6 @@
 			clock-frequency = <400000>;
 			dmas = <&blsp_dma 14>, <&blsp_dma 15>;
 			dma-names = "tx", "rx";
-			pinctrl-0 = <&i2c_0_pins>;
-			pinctrl-names = "default";
 			status = "disabled";
 		};
 
